003cli\u003e Use manufacturer\u0026#39;s software like SeaTools or third-party utilities like CrystalDiskInfo to assess hard drive health. \u003c/li\u003e\n \u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eEveryone generates a huge amount of data daily, and it needs to be stored securely in our devices\u0026#39; storage. But whether that\u0026#39;s an \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-external-hard-drives-mac/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eexternal drive used on a Mac\u003c/a\u003e, a \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-nas-hard-drive/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehard drive inside a NAS\u003c/a\u003e, or an \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-ssd-for-gaming/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSSD inside a Windows PC\u003c/a\u003e, our storage drives won\u0026#39;t last forever, even if we want our data to. There are many utilities for checking the built-in S.M.A.R.T. monitoring data that every hard drive and SSD produces, but how often should you check that data to avoid failing drives? Let\u0026#39;s answer that, and show you which tools to use to check your hard drive\u0026#39;s health.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"7432-4fcf-ae7eeda8c7de\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/signs-your-hard-drive-might-be-dying/\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"4080\" height=\"2295\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A 1TB Seagate Barracuda HDD on a white surface\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/pxl_20240731_074639441-portrait.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/signs-your-hard-drive-might-be-dying/\" title=\"7 signs your hard drive might be dying\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e 7 signs your hard drive might be dying \u003c/a\u003e \u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003eHard drives aren\u0026#39;t known to last long. Here are some telltale signs that yours might be at the end of the line.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"when-to-check-your-hard-drive-39-s-health\"\u003e When to check your hard drive\u0026#39;s health \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"often-but-not-too-often\"\u003e Often, but not too often \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhile it might be harder to find a new PC with a \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/6-reasons-why-you-shouldnt-use-a-hard-drive-in-2023/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emechanical hard drive (HDD)\u003c/a\u003e these days, that doesn\u0026#39;t mean they\u0026#39;re gone. With the average lifespan of an HDD being five years, plenty will still be in active use, and that\u0026#39;s not counting \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/want-to-set-up-a-home-media-server-heres-everything-you-need/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emedia servers\u003c/a\u003e or \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-nas/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eNAS devices\u003c/a\u003e, where the large capacities of HDDs still reign supreme. All of these drives have in-built monitoring for overall health, as well as things like reallocated sectors which indicate a failure might be coming. SSDs are less prone to some of the things that damage HDDs, but also wear over time and many of the monitoring programs still apply.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg\" data-img-desc=\"\u0026#34;Source: XDA\u0026#34;\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Seagate IronWolf 16TB hard drive.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2022/11/seagate-ironwolf-16tb-hdd-hero.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eSource: XDA\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere aren\u0026#39;t any concrete rules about when to check your hard drive\u0026#39;s health, but it\u0026#39;s wise to check regularly so you get advance warning of any potential failing drives. I like to check once every month or two, but if any of the following symptoms occur I\u0026#39;ll check straight away so I can stave off the potential of data loss.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e Slowly loading files or folders \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Drive disappears from Disk Management \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Strange noises like clicking, chirping, or screeching sounds from the drive \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Notifications of files not being accessible \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Increasing application crashes \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e BSODs or boot failures \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the testing from either the inbuilt pass/fail, the manufacturer\u0026#39;s own software or third-party utilities shows bad sectors, lots of reallocated sectors, or any numbers next to the other attributes that have \u0026#34;error\u0026#34; in their names, I\u0026#39;ll order a replacement drive and start on saving my data elsewhere. To check, I tend to prefer the manufacturer\u0026#39;s software, as it can tell me if I need to update drive firmware and other potential issues.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e Seagate has \u003ca href=\"https://www.seagate.com/in/en/support/downloads/seatools/#downloads\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSeaTools\u003c/a\u003e, \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e WD and SanDisk have \u003ca href=\"https://support-in.wd.com/app/products/downloads/softwaredownloads\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eWestern Digital Dashboard\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Adata has \u003ca href=\"https://www.adata.com/us/support/downloads/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAdata SSD Toolbox\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Samsung has \u003ca href=\"https://semiconductor.samsung.com/consumer-storage/support/tools/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSamsung Magician\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Kingston has \u003ca href=\"https://www.kingston.com/en/support/technical/ssdmanager\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSSD Manager\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBut if you prefer third-party, you can use CrystalDiskInfo, which will show the detailed S.M.A.R.T. data for your drive. Just be warned that not every attribute is supported by every hard drive manufacturer, and the list of attributes used by SSDs is even smaller.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"b931-4a03-a0d4f4fc751d\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/check-hard-drive-health-windows/\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A Seagate IronWolf NAS 4TB hard drive kept next to a WD Blue 500GB hard drive\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/img_20231201_205158-1.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/check-hard-drive-health-windows/\" title=\"3 easy ways to check hard drive health on Windows\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e 3 easy ways to check hard drive health on Windows \u003c/a\u003e \u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf your hard drive is showing symptoms of failure, use these tools to check its health\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"keep-your-data-safe-by-periodically-checking-your-hard-drive-health\"\u003e Keep your data safe by periodically checking your hard drive health \u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"An image of a Kingstone SSD kept adjacent to a WD hard drive.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/09/storage-drives.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKeeping an eye on the health of your storage drives is essential for not having to pay for expensive \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/what-is-data-restoration-how-does-it-work/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003edata restoration services\u003c/a\u003e. If any of the drive monitoring tools say anything other than OK, it\u0026#39;s time to order a replacement drive, and save your data from the failing drive. When doing so, go into the drive and copy your most important data first, onto another storage drive. Then, try doing a full disk image of the failing drive, so you have a full copy saved when your new replacement drive arrives. It\u0026#39;s essential to do the smaller copy of crucial data first, as you don\u0026#39;t want to risk straining the hard drive and having a failure while doing a full-disk copy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"c354-4623-a631d7ec48e8\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/here-are-the-6-best-tools-for-testing-your-storage-drives/\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"3840\" height=\"2160\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A person holding two external HDDs and an SSD in front of the Milk-V Jupiter\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/milk-v-jupier-nas-2.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/here-are-the-6-best-tools-for-testing-your-storage-drives/\" title=\"Here are the 6 best tools for testing your storage drives\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e Here are the 6 best tools for testing your storage drives \u003c/a\u003e \u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003eIs your storage drive acting up? These 6 tools can tell you what\u0026#39;s wrong\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n    \n        \n\n    \n\n        \n\n\n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
